  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "Managing the accounts you follow on Instagram can help streamline your feed and ensure you\u2019re engaging with content that truly interests you. While Instagram doesn\u2019t offer a built-in feature for bulk unfollowing, there are several methods you can use to quickly unfollow multiple accounts. Below are some effective approaches:\n\n## **1. Manual Unfollowing Within the Instagram App**\n\nWhile it might be time-consuming for large numbers of accounts, manually unfollowing ensures you maintain control and comply with Instagram\u2019s terms of service. Here's how:\n\n### **On Mobile (iOS and Android):**\n\n1. **Open Instagram** and navigate to your profile by tapping your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n2. **Tap on \"Following\"** to view the list of accounts you\u2019re following.\n3. **Scroll through the list** to find the account you want to unfollow.\n4. **Tap the \u201cFollowing\u201d button** next to their name. It will change to \u201cFollow,\u201d indicating you\u2019ve unfollowed them.\n5. **Repeat** the process for each account you wish to unfollow.\n\n### **On Desktop:**\n\n1. **Go to Instagram.com** and log in to your account.\n2. **Click on your profile picture** in the top right corner and select \u201cProfile.\u201d\n3. **Click on \"Following\"** to see the list of accounts you follow.\n4. **Hover over the \u201cFollowing\u201d button** next to the account you want to unfollow and click \u201cUnfollow.\u201d\n5. **Repeat** as needed for other accounts.\n\n## **2. Using Third-Party Apps and Services**\n\nSeveral third-party applications and browser extensions claim to help manage your Instagram following by allowing bulk unfollowing. **However, exercise caution** when using these tools for the following reasons:\n\n- **Security Risks:** Providing your Instagram credentials to third-party apps can jeopardize your account\u2019s security.\n- **Violation of Instagram\u2019s Terms of Service:** Instagram discourages the use of automated tools for actions like mass unfollowing. Using such tools can result in temporary restrictions or even permanent bans on your account.\n- **Privacy Concerns:** Some apps may misuse your data or bombard you with unwanted ads.\n\n**If you still consider using third-party tools**, ensure they are reputable and read reviews thoroughly. Always prioritize your account\u2019s security and be aware of the potential risks involved.\n\n## **3. Automating with Scripts (Advanced Users)**\n\nFor those with technical expertise, writing scripts to automate unfollowing can be an option. **However, this method carries significant risks:**\n\n- **Complexity:** Requires knowledge of programming and Instagram\u2019s API.\n- **Risk of Suspension:** Automated actions can flag your account for suspicious activity, leading to limitations or bans.\n- **Maintenance:** Instagram frequently updates its platform, which can break your scripts and require constant adjustments.\n\n**Recommendation:** This method is generally not recommended unless you have a specific need and the technical skills to implement it safely.\n\n## **4. Best Practices for Managing Your Following List**\n\nInstead of bulk unfollowing, consider these strategies to maintain a curated following list:\n\n- **Regularly Review Your Following:** Periodically go through the accounts you follow and unfollow those that no longer provide value or interest.\n- **Use \u201cClose Friends\u201d Feature:** For content you want to prioritize without unfollowing, add accounts to your Close Friends list for more personalized feeds.\n- **Engage Selectively:** Interact more with accounts you genuinely enjoy to naturally prioritize their content in your feed.\n\n## **Conclusion**\n\nWhile Instagram doesn\u2019t support bulk unfollowing natively, managing your following list manually ensures compliance with platform policies and maintains account security. If you choose to use third-party tools, proceed with caution and be fully aware of the associated risks. Regular maintenance of your following list can enhance your Instagram experience by keeping your feed relevant and engaging.",
